subtitle.en: Our premises have 24 hours camera surveillance connected to an alarm system. The doors are locked using a smart lock which members can access using a personal NFC bracelet. Based on this we know exactly when and who has been in the shop and is doing what. We also offer a proprietary board locking system so rest assured your board is safe at Surf Garage.
subtitle.es: Nuestras instalaciones cuentan con cmaras de vigilancia 24 horas conectadas a un sistema de alarma. Las puertas se cierran con una cerradura inteligente a la que los socios pueden acceder mediante una pulsera NFC personal. Gracias a esto, sabemos exactamente cundo y quin ha estado en la tienda y qu est haciendo. Tambin ofrecemos un sistema patentado de bloqueo de tablas, por lo que puedes estar tranquilo sabiendo que tu tabla est segura en Surf Garage.

subtitle.en: Do you live far away from Cicer and you always find yourself driving around Guanarteme looking for parking? Do you often drag your board all the way from the top floor of your building and bump it everywhere on your way down. Leave your board with us in a safe/secure place. You only have to care about catching waves, while your board is waiting for you 3 minutes from surf. Lock your phone and wallet in the lockers. Take a nice shower after surf and leave your wetsuit to dry at Surf Garage.
subtitle.es: Vives lejos de la Cicer y siempre te encuentras dando vueltas por Guanarteme buscando aparcamiento? A menudo bajas tu tabla desde el ltimo piso de tu edificio y la golpeas por todas partes al bajar? Deja tu tabla con nosotros en un lugar seguro. Solo debes preocuparte por coger olas, mientras tu tabla te espera a 3 minutos de surf. Guarda tu telfono y tu cartera en nuestras taquillas. Toma una buena ducha despus de surfear y deja tu neopreno secando en Surf Garage.

description.en: Surf Garage is world's first of its kind self-service surf board storage facility in the city of Las Palmas de Gran Canaria. This city is built along a 2km stretch of beach with one of the longest beach walking paths of any city in the world. And guess what, there are several surfable waves right in the city centre all year round..

content.value: Surf Garage was founded in 2022 by Sam due to a personal need. He and his friends needed a place to store their surf boards close to the waves.
Sam is is a typical lazy surfer who loves to ride big longboards. Longboards are the surfing equivalent of a harley davidson. Big, heavy and cruisyyyy (is that a word?)..

He used to store his big boards at his apartment on the second floor of a building. Carrying his board down the tiny stairway bumping it on every turn wasn't so much fun. After dozens of dings and angry neighbors complaining about little drops of water all over the staircase, he decided to open a self-service surfboard storage space.
The Making of Surf Garage

The space where Surf Garage exists today used to be a place to buy/sell gold. It took 6 months of sweat, tears, dust, beers, pain, happiness, breaking, building, drawing, painting, and looking for solutions on the internet to transform it to a surfboard storage space.

As the project came along, Sam decided to combine his passion of phography and surf. The left wall in the shop was in pretty bad shape with tons of holes in it. Apparently it was built from the sand from Las Canteras. Up until a couple of decades ago, all of Guanarteme was apparently just a bunch of sand dunes.

So instead of repairing the wall, we covered it with surf photography and artwork. And then in 2024, we went ahead and created an online marketplace for artwork from local Canarian Artists. 
Check it out
https://surfgarage.art

description.en: Fuerteventura is a canvas where ocean swells paint endless patterns on golden shores. The rhythmic crash of waves against volcanic cliffs creates a symphony, drawing surfers to dance upon liquid walls of turquoise and emerald. Each break tells a story, wild and untamed, under a sun-drenched sky that blends seamlessly with the horizon.
description.es: Fuerteventura es un canvas donde los oleajes del ocano pintan patrones infinitos sobre orillas doradas. El ritmo de las olas rompiendo contra los acantilados volcnicos crea una sinfona, atrayendo a los surfistas a danzar sobre paredes lquidas de turquesa y esmeralda. Cada rompiente cuenta una historia, salvaje e indomable, bajo un cielo baado por el sol que se funde con el horizonte.

shortDescription.en: Sam is a photographer, entrepreneur and surfer based in the Canary Islands. He loves to shoot candid shots of surfers, landscapes, beaches, sunsets and everything else related to the ocean.

description.en:
Sam is a photographer, entrepreneur, surfer and coder based in the Canary Islands. Sam bought his first Nikon DSLR when he was 21 and he found his passion for phography while travelling around Asia, Latin America and Europe. As a solo traveller, Sam's camera was his best travel buddy and he shot everything that captured his eye during his travels.

Sam often takes his camera out when the surf is too big. He loves to shoot candid shots, landscapes, surfers, beaches, sunsets and everything else related to the ocean.
description.es:
Sam es un fotgrafo, emprendedor, surfista y desarrollador basado en las Islas Canarias. Sam compr su primera cmara (un Nikon DSLR) cuando tena 21 aos y encontr su pasin por la fotografa mientras viajaba por Asia, Amrica Latina y Europa. Viajando solo, la cmara era su mejor compaera de viaje y sacaba todo lo que captaba su atencin durante sus viajes.

Sam suele sacar su cmara cuando las olas son demasiado grandes. Le encanta tomar fotografas espontneas, paisajes, surfistas, playas, atardeceres y todo lo relacionado con el ocano.

description.en:
Irene Polinelli, born in Verona, Italy in 1995.

She started painting, creating and taking photographs since her childhood. After a journey of scientific studies, she studied and graduated as a painter at the Venice Academy of Fine Arts.

In 2019 she moved to Las Palmas de Gran Canaria where she continued her training for a year, doing a photography and a fashion course at the Gran Canaria Art School.

In her career she creates different types of art: paintings on canvas, on clothing, murals, embroiders fabrics and canvases, digital and analog illustrations, collages and graphics.
description.es:
Irene Polinelli, nacida en Verona, Italia en 1995.

Comenz a pintar, crear y tomar fotografas desde su infancia. Tras un periplo de estudios cientficos, estudi y se gradu como pintora en la Academia de Bellas Artes de Venecia.

En 2019 se traslada a Las Palmas de Gran Canaria donde contina su formacin durante un ao realizando un curso de fotografa y moda en la Escuela de Arte de Gran Canaria.

En su carrera crea diferentes tipos de arte: pinturas sobre lienzo, sobre ropa, murales, bordados de telas y lienzos, ilustraciones digitales y analgicas, collages y grficas.

description.en: Gran Canaria is one of the best canary islands for surfing, along with Lanzarote, Fuerteventura and Tenerife. This is your ultimate guide to surf in Gran Canaria. We'll show you the best surf spots as well as the best tips on how and when to surf them, including swells, tides and other important conditions.
description.es: Gran Canaria es una de las mejores islas canarias para practicar surf, junto con Lanzarote, Fuerteventura y Tenerife. Esta es tu gua definitiva para el surf en Gran Canaria. Te mostraremos los mejores spots, as como los mejores consejos sobre cmo y cundo surfearlos, incluidos oleajes, mareas y otras condiciones importantes.

content.value: When to surf in Gran Canaria
You can surf in Gran Canaria all year long, being the best season from October to April, when the north swells are the strongest and the summer winds calm down.
Summer can also be very good and gentle for beginners, as the swells are milder and more suitable for learners.
Surf spots in Gran Canaria
Most surf spots in Gran Canaria are located on the
north shore
. The NE to NW swells coming from the North Atlantic are almost constant, making it the most reliable and consistent part of the island.
Las Palmas
, located on the NE tip of the island has a collection of surf breaks suitable for all levels.
The
East Coast
has a few breaks that can work on NE to SE swells, although they dont tend to work often, as Africa is very close to the East.
The
south

has some excellent surfing spots, arguably the best of the island. To work it needs any kind of south swell or a very big NE swell that wraps around the island. South swells are not common, but they happen every few weeks.
The west holds no breaks, besides being very inaccesible.

Surf Gran Canaria - East Coast
Surf Gran Canaria - South Coast
Surfboard rental and storage
Most surf rentals and shops are in the Cicer area in Las Palmas city. You can find some other surf shops and rentals in the south, in Playa del Ingls and Maspalomas, but surf there is less frequent.
If you need storage for your equipment just 3 minutes walking from the waves of La Cicer beach,
Surf Garage
is your best option. We offer the best facilities and the most flexible hours, as well as high quality second hand gear for sale.
Cundo surfear en Gran Canaria
Se puede hacer surf en Gran Canaria durante todo el ao, siendo la mejor temporada de Octubre a Abril, cuando el oleaje del norte es ms fuerte y los vientos del verano se calman.
El verano tambin puede ser muy bueno y suave para los principiantes, ya que las olas son ms suaves y ms adecuadas para los que se estn iniciando en este deporte.
Spots para surfear en Gran Canaria
La mayora de los spots para practicar surf en Gran Canaria se encuentran en la
costa norte
. El oleaje del NE al NO proveniente del Atlntico Norte es casi constante, lo que la convierte en la parte ms confiable y consistente de la isla.
Las Palmas de Gran Canaria
, ubicada en el extremo NE de la isla, tiene una coleccin de spots y olas para todos los niveles.
La costa este
tiene algunas olas que pueden funcionar con oleajes de NE a SE, aunque no suelen funcionar con frecuencia, ya que frica est muy cerca y el mar suele estar ms calmado en este estrecho.
El sur

tiene excelentes lugares para practicar surf, posiblemente los mejores de la isla. Para funcionar necesita cualquier tipo de swell del sur o un swell muy grande del NE que envuelva la isla. Las marejadas del sur no son comunes, pero ocurren cada pocas semanas.
El oeste no tiene ninguna ola destacable, adems de ser muy inaccesible.
Surf Gran Canaria - Las Palmas
Surf Gran Canaria - Norte
Surf Gran Canaria - Este
Surf Gran Canaria - Sur
Alquiler y almacenamiento de tablas de surf

La mayora de los alquileres y tiendas de surf se encuentran en la zona de Cicer en la ciudad de Las Palmas. Puedes encontrar otras tiendas y alquileres de surf en el sur, en Playa del Ingls y Maspalomas, pero el surf all es menos frecuente.
Si necesitas un sitio para gurdar tu equipo a tan solo 3 minutos andando de las olas de la playa de La Cicer,
Surf Garage
es tu mejor opcin. Ofrecemos las mejores instalaciones y los horarios ms flexibles, as como venta de material de segunda mano de alta calidad.

description.en: Las Palmas has some of the best surf spots in the island suitable for all levels, from the gentle Cicer beach break to the unforgiving perfect barrels of Confital.

content.value: La Cicer

Level: beginner to expert
Tide: low  mid- high
Crowd: high
Board type: longboard, shortboard
Forecast:
https://es.surf-forecast.com/breaks/La-Cicer/forecasts/latest/six_day
La Cicer is a collection of different breaks at the SW end of las Canteras beach, which is the main beach of Las Palmas.

Swell here is very consistent and the sandy bottom makes it an ideal place for beginners and surf schools. Depending on ther strength of the swell, La Cicer can go from beginner to expert level. It's accessibility and the fact that it's located right in Las Palmas main beach attracts big crowds, but its not known for being an unfriendly place.
All the way to the SW tip there's a point break called Los Muellitos, which tends to produce a wave suitable for long-boarders. Best to surf in mid to low tide.

From there to the East, there's a series of beach breaks. Waves here break in all directions and are prone to close outs, but the reliablity and the consistency of the swell make up for it. Best to surf in mid to high tide.
Summer can have flat periods, but there is swell all year long.
El Lloret

Level: advanced - expert
Tide: low  mid
Crowd: high
Board type: shortboard
Forecast:
https://es.surf-forecast.com/breaks/El-Lloret/forecasts/latest/six_day

This point break produces a beautiful, powerful right hand wave suitable for shortboards that is very cherished by the locals. Going in and out is tricky because of the rocks and currents, and it's only surfable during mid  low tide. Doesnt work with small swells, as there are many rocks sticking out near the shore and needs to be big enough for the wave to break further back.
The locals are very protective of this spot, so go only if you're sure you have the level required and be mindful and respectful.
La Barra

Level: advanced - expert
Tide: high
Crowd: mid
Board type: shortboard
Forecast:
https://es.surf-forecast.com/breaks/La-Barra/forecasts/latest/six_day
La Barra is a reef covering two thirds of Las Canteras beach. When the tide is high, the reef is under water and produces a series of short waves suitable for bodyboards and shortboards.
It can break in many different spots depending of the direction and size of the swell, so take a look oatwhere the locals are.
Confital

Level: expert
Tide: high
Crowd: mid  high
Board type: shortboard
Forecast:
https://www.surf-forecast.com/breaks/Confital/forecasts/latest/six_day

Possibly the most famous and best wave in the island, Confital is a fast, hollow, barreling wave, considered one of the best in Europe. The downside? Localism is really bad, so its not recommended to go there unless you're really good at surfing and you know the local crowd.
The wave is shallow and breaks over a rock slab, so it can be only surfed at high tide. It's the only wave in the north of Gran Canaria that can get offshore winds when it blows from the N  NE.
Go back to Surf Spots Gran Canaria

title.en: Surf Gran Canaria - The North Coast

description.en: The North coast hosts some of the best and most consistent surf in Gran Canaria. It receives constant swell from the North Atlantic and holds loads of excellent surf and bodyboard waves. All the spots are very close to each other and very accessible from the road.

content.value: Quintanilla

Level: intermediate - expert
Tide: mid
Crowd: mid  high
Board type: shortboard
Forecast:
https://www.surf-forecast.com/breaks/Quintanilla

Quintanilla is the first spot you run into driving west from Las Palmas. Access is easy, through a sandy beach. The fast, left hand wave breaks aproximately 100m from the shore over a rocky bottom, so its best to avoid the low tide.

Quintanilla tends to get the most of the north swells and the biggest waves in the north, so its a good indicator of whats happening in the rest of the spots. If its not surfable here, it will rarely be surfable anywhere else down the road.
Los Enanos

Level: beginner - expert
Tide: mid - low
Crowd: mid - high
Season: Year round
Board type: shortboard
Forecast:
https://es.surf-forecast.com/breaks/Los-Enanos/forecasts/latest/six_day

A beach break that also picks a lot of swell. Can get very packed when La Cicer is too small and people from the city go look for accessible waves in the north. Waves here usually pack a good punch, so a lot of paddling is usually required. Surfable at low to mid tide.
Molokai

Level: beginner - expert
Tide: mid - low
Crowd: mid  high
Board type: shortboard
Forecast:
https://es.surf-forecast.com/breaks/Los-Enanos/forecasts/latest/six_day

This beach break is just west of Los Enanos and you can even paddle between them. Waves are similar to Los Enanos, although usually Molokai has the edge when it comes longer, mellower waves. Depending on the size of the swell, it can be very gentle or it can turn into a very intense experience, so its suitable for all levels depending on the conditions.
Same as Los Enanos, it can get crowded when Las Palmas is small. A lot of surf schools like to come here in search of mellow, accessible waves.
Surfable at low to mid tide.
Boquines

Level: intermediate - expert
Tide: mid - low
Crowd: mid
Board type: shortboard
Forecast:
https://es.surf-forecast.com/breaks/Boquines/forecasts/latest/six_day

One of the most accessible pointbreaks, it produces a long, clean right hander suitable for shortboards during N  NE swells. Best to surf at mid to low tide. Be careful of the rocks, as it can become shallow very quick when the tide is too low and the swell is not big enough. Going in and out can be tricky because of the rocks and urchins, but not as much as other spots such as El Lloret.
El Picacho

Level: intermediate - expert
Tide: mid - low
Crowd: mid 
Board type: longboard
Forecast:
https://www.surf-forecast.com/breaks/El-Paso_1/forecasts/latest/six_day
Just west of Boquines, this point break has a long right and shorter left, usually more suitable for longboards.
Access is easy through a pebble beach and its best at mid tide.
Derecha del Roque

Level: advanced - expert
Tide: mid - low
Crowd: mid
Board type: shortboard
Forecast:
https://es.surf-forecast.com/breaks/El-Roque/forecasts/latest/six_day

Derecha del Roque holds maybe the longest wave in the north coast when the conditions are right. It's a right hand point break right in front of El Altillo town suitable for shortboards. Entrance and exit are tricky beacause of the rocks and urchins, and the wave can become really powerful on bigger swells. Only recommended for advanced surfers. Surfable at mid to low tide.
Izquierda del Paso

Level: intermediate - expert
Tide: mid - high
Crowd: mid 
Board type: shortboard
La Izquierda del Paso is a left point break just west of Derecha del Roque, in front of El Paso village. Best to surf at high tide because of the rocks sticking out. Doesnt work on eastern swells.
El Bunker

Level: intermediate - expert
Tide: mid - high
Crowd: mid 
Board type: shortboard

This rock bottom left hand point break picks up less swell than poher spots around, so it tends to hold the size when everything else is too big. Beware of the rocks and urchin. Surfable at high tide.
Vagabundos

Level: beginner - expert
Tide: mid - low
Crowd: mid 
Board type: shortboard
Forecast:
https://es.surf-forecast.com/breaks/Vagabundo/forecasts/latest/six_day

This beach break is located right in front of San Felipe town. The two main waves are a left hander at the far west end and a right hander on the east end. The waves can be powerful and fast, but they can hold the shape very well if conditions are right. Passing the break can be a challenge on bigger days. Best to surf at mid to low tide.
Summer months offer the best conditions for beginners. Its a swell magnet during this time and sometimes the only spot with waves.
Go back to Surf Spots Gran Canaria
Surf Gran Canaria  Galdar

If you drive further on the north coast past Vagabundos, you can't help but notice this village of Galdar on the foothills of a volcano. Right behind this volcano there are a bunch of world class surf spots, one of which holds the yearly bodyboard championships "El Fronton King"!
El Frontn

Level: expert
Tide: high
Crowd: mid  high
Board type: shortboard
Forecast:
https://es.surf-forecast.com/breaks/El-Fronton/forecasts/latest/six_day

More of a bodyboard wave, this powerful, fast, barrelling wave should only be approached by experts. Breaks over a very shallow rock slab, so it's only surfable at high tide. International bodyboard championships are celebrated here every year.
La Guancha

Level: expert
Tide: high
Crowd: mid  high
Board type: shortboard
Forecast:
https://es.surf-forecast.com/breaks/La-Guancha/forecasts/latest/six_day
Right in front of El Agujero natural pools, La Guancha has lefts and right breaking over a shallow rock reef.
El Agujero

Level: expert
Tide: low - mid
Crowd: mid 
Board type: shortboard
A solid right hand barrel just west of La Guancha. Needs a big swell to work and breaks over a shallow reef. Surfable at low to mid tide.
Go back to Surf Spots Gran Canaria

title.en: Surf Gran Canaria  The East Coast

description.en: The East coast, mostly known for its world famous wind-surfing spots also has some less crowded surf spots. Because of the islands geography, the east coast is often very windy but every now and then when the stars line up, the wind dies, east swells hit the island and a few good spots start firing.

content.value: La Laja

Level: beginner - expert
Tide: mid-low
Crowd: mid 
Board type: shortboard
Forecast:
https://es.wisuki.com/forecast/2811/la-laja

La Laja has two different breaks. On the north end theres a hollow, fast left hand wave breaking over a shallow volcanic reef, more suitable for bodyboarders. On the SE end, theres a beach break that produces a short, fast wave that can be very fun when its not too big or windy. Surfable at mid-low-tide.
Playa del Hombre
Level
: beginner - advanced
Tide
: mid
Crowd
: mid  high
Board type
: shortboard
Forecast
Playa del Hombre Surf Forecast

With the right conditions, waves at this beach break can be very good. Surf schools in the south of the island like to go there, so it's usually crowded with beginners even when conditions are not ideal. Surfable at mid tide.
Las Terrazas
Level
: beginner - advanced
Tide
: any
Crowd
: mid
Board type
: shortboard, mid-length
Right behind the shopping centre of Las Terrazas, there is a right hander that works every now and then. But when it does, its a pleasure to ride it.
Mosca Point

Level: advanced - expert
Tide: low
Crowd: mid
Board type: longboard, shortboard
Forecast:
https://es.surf-forecast.com/breaks/Mosca-Point/forecasts/latest/six_day

Long left hand point break that works when the swell is big and the wind is calm (it's in windiest part of the island so it doesn't happen often). Sharp rocks at the end of the wave. Surfable at low tide.
Pozo Izquierdo

Level: intermediate - expert
Tide: low - high
Crowd: mid
Board type: shortboard
Forecast:
https://es.surf-forecast.com/breaks/Pozo-Izquierdo/forecasts/latest/six_day
Again in the windiest part of the island (Pozo izquierdo is the windsurf capital of Gran Canaria), when the wind drops a right hand beach break forms at the south end of the beach.
Juan Grande

Level: beginner - expert
Tide: low
Crowd: mid 
Board type: longboard, shortboard
Forecast:
https://www.worldbeachguide.com/spain/surf/juan-grande.htm
Long pebble beach with several peaks that work at low tide.
Go back to Surf Spots Gran Canaria

title.en: Surf Gran Canaria  The South Coast

description.en: The south of the island is sheltered from both the swells and the winds from the North Atlantic. But the swells from the South Atlantic do hit every few weeks, which combined with the offshore or glassy conditions, produce some of the best rides on the island.

content.value: Playa del Ingls

Level: beginner - advanced
Tide: low - high
Crowd: high
Board type: longboard, shortboard
Forecast:
https://es.surf-forecast.com/breaks/Playadel-Inglas/forecasts/latest/six_day
This very long beach holds many small beach breaks, usually better during summer months. When it works, which is not often, its usually crowded with beginners and swimmers.
El Faro de Maspalomas

Level: beginner - advanced
Tide: low - high
Crowd: high
Board type: longboard, shortboard
Forecast:
https://es.surf-forecast.com/breaks/Maspalomas/forecasts/latest/six_day

Same as Playa de Inlgls, surf here is better during summer months and consists of small beachbreaks. When a big swells hits though, the small beach breaks can become a very nice, mellow right hander. Often crowded with schools and swimmers.
Arguineguin

Level: intermediate - advanced
Tide: low - mid
Crowd: mid  high
Board type: longboard, shortboard
Forecast:
https://es.surf-forecast.com/breaks/Arguineguin/forecasts/latest/six_day
The cradle of surf in Gran Canaria. This was the first surfing spot in the island, adopted by a hippie community that made Arguineguin its home back in the 1960's.

Depending on the direction of the swell, two waves can form. And they are both superb when it's firing. If the swell is SW, a faster right hander forms on the west end of the beach. If the swell is SE, a mellower left hander forms to the east, towards the cement factory. It`s a very popular spot for longboarders and shortboarders alike.
Surfable during mid to low tide.
Go back to Surf Spots Gran Canaria

description.es:
Jake comenz su pasin por la ilustracin mientras viajaba por Mxico. Se dio cuenta de que alguien venda pegatinas de su lugar favorito (chacahua, Mxico) y pens que debera intentarlo tambin. En el primer da vendi todo su cartel de viaje y su pegatina de Chacahua, con lo que pag un par de noches en hamaca y desayuno. Desde entonces ha ido dibujando todos los lugares que ha visitado y que le han gustado.

Jake le encanta las Islas Canarias y dibuja cada lugar que visita en las islas, incluidos los recuerdos personales de cada lugar. Ahora, Jake est intentando mudarse permanentemente a Gran Canaria, donde podr concentrarse en sus carteles de viajes retro e ilustraciones de surf.

description.en: Surf Garage Art Collective is a collective of artists based in the Canary Islands who love sharing their lives, travels and experiences through the means of photos and illustrations.

content.value: Our mission is to support emerging artists, helping them gain exposure and income from their work. Artists are paid a commission from every sale.
Eco Friendly

Surf Garage Art Collective is a small home run eco friendly business. All the artwork is printed on demand in the Canary Islands on eco-friendly fine art paper and shipped to you in re-cycled paper tubes.
History
Surf Garage

" was founded in 2022 as a first of its kind self-service surf board storage facility in the city of Las Palmas on the island of Gran Canaria. It allowed surfers who live in the suburbs to store their boards and wetsuits in a safe comfortable space close to the waves. You can simply show up, change, grab your board and go surf. Come back take a nice hot shower and go grab a coffee in the city. No need to walk your surfboard 10 miles with a dripping wet wetsuit on.
We always had lots of artwork from local artists hanging on our walls. Tons of people always kept asking us if they could buy the stuff.

So in 2023 Sam (the owner) decided to combine his three passions: surf, photography and web development. And the idea of Surf Garage Art Collective was born. He wanted to showcase his photopraphy and also give other artists a chance to showcase their work. After a year of on and off coding, Surf Garage Art Collective was finally launched on 1 Jan 2024.
Physical Store
We don't have any physical stores, but if you are in Las Palmas come say hi at our board storage space -
Surf Garage Guardatablas

description.en: Become a part of Surf Garage Art Collective

content.value: If you draw or shoot anything related to surf | beaches | palm trees | sunsets and would like to be part of the Surf Garage Art Collective, get in touch (scroll down till the end and fill in the contact form)..

We take care of everything from uploading and managing your digital files on the site, marketing, selling, printing and shipping. So you can do what you love doing the most! You will still own all rights to your artwork.
We give back up to 50% of our profits to the artists.

description.en: All artwork is proudly printed on demand in the Canary Islands (to avoid waste) and packed in paper tubes made of recycled materials.

content.value: Printing Process

We use state of art modern printers, which have 12 unique eco-friendly inks that are sprayed directly on to fine art papers using precision nozzles, resulting in incredible pieces of art that last for many years to come.
Fine-Art Paper
We use fine art cotton paper 260gm (FSC certified paper from sustainably-managed forests)
Shipping
We ship to all over mainland Europe. Or free pick up at our shop in
Las Palmas de Gran Canaria
. Free shipping for orders above 60!
Bigger Sizes (bigger than A3)
If you would like to print some artwork in a size bigger than A3, please contact us. Based on the quality of the digital file, we may be able to print in bigger sizes.

shortDescription.en: Laurita Polvorilla is a photographer specializing in surf and lifestyle. Her work stands out for its focus on soft textures, minimalism and an aesthetic that conveys calm and simplicity
shortDescription.es: Laurita Polvorilla es una fotografa especializada en surf y estilo de vida. Su trabajo destaca por su enfoque en texturas suaves, minimalismo y una esttica que transmite calma y sencillez.

description.en:
Born in Asturias and now rooted for the past seven years on the Mexican Pacific Coast, Laurita Polvorilla is a photographer specializing in surf and lifestyle. Her work stands out for its focus on soft textures, minimalism and an aesthetic that conveys calm and simplicity.

Laurita work emphasizes the majesty of the ocean, telling visual stories that go beyond the waves. With a unique ability to capture intimate and authentic moments, she reflects the deep connection between people and nature. Each image is a testimony to her passion for the sea and her dedication to capturing the beauty and serenity of coastal life.
description.es:
Nacida en Asturias y ahora arraigada desde hace siete aos en la Costa del Pacifico Mexicano, Laurita Polvorilla es una fotografa especializada en surf y estilo de vida. Su trabajo destaca por su enfoque en texturas suaves, minimalismo y una esttica que transmite calma y sencillez.

En sus fotografias, Laurita inmortaliza la majestuosidad del ocano, contando historias visuales que van mas alla de las olas. Con una habilidad Unica para capturar momentos intimos y autnticos, refleja la profunda conexidn entre las personas y la naturaleza. Cada imagen es un testimonio de su pasion por el mar y su dedicacin a capturar la belleza y serenidad de la vida costera.

description.en: La Palma, known as "La Isla Bonita," enchants with its lush forests, dramatic volcanic landscapes, and clear night skies perfect for stargazing. This UNESCO Biosphere Reserve offers pristine nature, picturesque villages and world-class hiking trails like the Ruta de los Volcanes.
description.es: La Palma, conocida como "La Isla Bonita," encanta con sus frondosos bosques, dramticos paisajes volcnicos y cielos despejados ideales para la observacin de estrellas. Esta Reserva de la Biosfera de la UNESCO ofrece naturaleza virgen, pueblos pintorescos y senderos de clase mundial como la Ruta de los Volcanes.
